reviews.text: Disappointed, normally you get topping on the pizza rolls. This time nothing, ordered pep, jalapeno, black olives, mushroom.
Ordered a gourmet spinach and garlic pizza with hot wings, both were delicious and ready for pick up right on time. We will definitely be ordering again.

I called the store and said the coupon code that was texted to me from Pizza Fino didn‚Äôt work when I entered it on their website.  She said that they‚Äôd honor it over the phone, no problem.  I gave her my order, she applied the coupon, food showed up quickly, hot and fresh.  Exceptional customer service, outstanding food and delivered fast.  Couldn‚Äôt ask for anything more.

We regularly order food here while at a shop a few doors down and it is delivered to us no problem. Tonight I walk in and instead of the usual cheery employee I deal with, there was someone else.

I was told to wait to order because she had a call on hold, which was fine. I placed my order, and asked if the food would be brought over as it always is and she said ‚Äúno‚Äù. I asked what do you mean, the other employees always do since it is literally a couple doors down and her response with attitude was ‚Äúwell she‚Äôs not working today!‚Äù. The saltiness of her response actually surprised me. I asked her what it would take to get it delivered and she said ‚Äúpay the delivery fee and the driver will bring it‚Äù.

I asked her if the driver was going to drive it two doors over and her response was essentially yes they would. Pretty negative experience in a place that has been overwhelming positive in the past. Never seen this employee before, so will definitely spend my money elsewhere if I see her working again. There‚Äôs plenty of other businesses in this strip that appreciate my business and if I‚Äôm craving pizza I will just order dominos if I see her at the counter.

The only thing good here is the pizza. Well, I don't know about the wings, but wings are hit or miss with pizza places. The cheesesticks had 0 crunch factor, and so did the onion rings. It was like a sloppy flour mixture, then lightly fried. The pizza was a delicacy, but I wouldn't go here for anything else. Below is my videos and pic review. Also the large pizza was more like a medium

customerMoodAnalysis.sentimentSummary: Customer opinions are divided. The 3.2/5 rating from 5 recent reviews suggests some great experiences mixed with areas needing attention.

strengthsPerceived: "Delicious gourmet spinach and garlic pizza and hot wings ready for pick up right on time" - SEO services can leverage this for better visibility
"Exceptional customer service, honoring coupon codes over the phone" - review management can highlight this positive aspect
"Food showed up quickly, hot and fresh" - social media marketing can showcase this strength
improvementOpportunities: Negative experience with customer service and inconsistency in delivery policy - review management can address this concern
Poor quality of non-pizza menu items (cheesesticks and onion rings) - social media marketing can improve this area
Lack of toppings on pizza rolls and size discrepancy of large pizza - Boostly marketing services can improve this
